headline: 3 Magnificent S&P 500 Dividend Stocks Down More Than 13% to Buy and Hold Forever
summary: The S&P 500 has sold off in recent weeks, tumbling more than 10% from its peak at one point.  Falling stock prices also increase dividend yields, and now's a great time to load up on some high-quality dividend stocks.  Kinder Morgan (NYSE: KMI), NextEra Energy (NYSE: NEE), and Prologis (NYSE: PLD) are all currently down more than 13% from their recent peaks.
